ldp / listdivertpattern       Lists patterns for Divert tasks

   Format:
      ;ldp                    Lists all patterns
      ;ldp <switch>           Lists patterns of a certain type
 
   Notes:
      The Divert task intercepts text received from the world and displays it in
         its own task window. 
      The patterns used are stored in the current world profile. This command
         lists those patterns. (See the help for ';adddivertpattern' for more 
         information about Divert task patterns.)

      If <switch> is specified, it can be any of the following:
         -t   Lists 'tell' patterns (and tell exception patterns)
         -e   Lists 'tell' patterns (and tell exception patterns)

         -s   Lists social patterns (and social exception patterns)
         -o   Lists social patterns (and social exception patterns)

         -c   Lists custom patterns (and custom exception patterns)
         -u   Lists custom patterns (and custom exception patterns)
         -x   Lists custom patterns (and custom exception patterns)
         
      If no <switch> is specified, all patterns are listed.
 
   User commands:
      ldp / listdivert / listdivertpattern
